1502
01:36:51,568 --> 01:36:55,129
Do you know why Mrs. Manion
requested a lie detector test?

1503
01:36:55,238 --> 01:36:57,138
- I know what she said.
- What?

1504
01:36:57,240 --> 01:37:01,006
She wanted everyone to believe her story
because she knew it'd help her husband.

1505
01:37:01,110 --> 01:37:02,873
Was that the only reason she gave?

1506
01:37:02,979 --> 01:37:07,279
Said she swore to her husband. Said she
wanted everyone else to believe it too.

1507
01:37:07,383 --> 01:37:09,283
One moment, please.

1508
01:37:13,022 --> 01:37:15,616
Ask him in what manner she swore.

1509
01:37:15,725 --> 01:37:19,024
Did Mrs. Manion say how
she had sworn to her husband?

1510
01:37:19,128 --> 01:37:23,064
Yes, sir. She said
she had sworn on a rosary.

1511
01:37:23,166 --> 01:37:28,001
This lane in the woods,
what's it used for, where does it go?

1512
01:37:28,104 --> 01:37:31,301
It used to be a logging road.
It doesn't go anyplace, just stops.

1513
01:37:31,407 --> 01:37:33,307
Who uses it now?

1514
01:37:33,409 --> 01:37:35,639
I think it's a road
kids drive down to park.

1515
01:37:35,745 --> 01:37:38,373
- You mean it's a lovers' lane?
- I think so.

1516
01:37:38,481 --> 01:37:41,348
- The witness is yours.
- No more questions.

1517
01:37:41,451 --> 01:37:44,887
- The witness may step down.
- In view of evidence concerning rape...

1518
01:37:44,988 --> 01:37:47,149
which Your Honor
has ruled admissible...

1519
01:37:47,257 --> 01:37:49,487
the prosecution asks for
a 30-minute recess...

1520
01:37:49,592 --> 01:37:52,584
in order to bring in another witness
we had not anticipated using?

1521
01:37:52,695 --> 01:37:55,391
All right.
We'll take a 30-minute recess.

1522
01:37:55,498 --> 01:37:56,988
Recess.

1523
01:38:03,940 --> 01:38:06,374
Why didn't you tell me
about that rosary?

1524
01:38:07,710 --> 01:38:09,610
I forgot it.

1525
01:38:09,712 --> 01:38:14,274
We didn't forget it. Manny said maybe
we shouldn't tell that again.

1526
01:38:14,384 --> 01:38:18,286
It might have looked like something
else... like I didn't believe her.

1527
01:38:19,756 --> 01:38:24,625
- How much more didn't you tell me?
- We told you everything else.

1528
01:38:24,727 --> 01:38:26,752
Is that right, Laura?

1529
01:38:26,863 --> 01:38:29,024
Oh, yes, everything else.

1530
01:38:29,132 --> 01:38:31,293
Now get this, both of you.

1531
01:38:31,401 --> 01:38:35,337
When you get up on that stand,
I want you to tell the truth.

1532
01:38:35,438 --> 01:38:37,929
I don't want you to tell anything
but the truth.

1533
01:38:38,041 --> 01:38:42,910
Don't try and lie or conceal anything
or you get skinned alive.

1534
01:38:43,012 --> 01:38:45,242
This fellow Dancer's gonna move in.

1535
01:39:06,202 --> 01:39:09,763
Dr. Dompierre, did you have occasion
to come to the county jail...

1536
01:39:09,872 --> 01:39:12,238
on the night of August 15 this year?

1537
01:39:12,342 --> 01:39:14,970
- I did.
- Who called you to the jail?

1538
01:39:15,078 --> 01:39:18,479
- The police authorities.
- What did they want you to do?

1539
01:39:18,581 --> 01:39:21,550
They wanted me to make a test
for the presence of sperm...

1540
01:39:21,651 --> 01:39:24,017
on the person
of a Mrs. Frederick Manion.

1541
01:39:24,120 --> 01:39:27,920
- I made the test.
- What was your conclusion?

1542
01:39:28,024 --> 01:39:31,152
- Negative. There was none.
- Your witness.

1543
01:39:32,629 --> 01:39:37,464
In making these tests, did you notice
